FINOVA NETWORK ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS
================================================================================

This software is part of the Finova Network ecosystem, a decentralized social-fi
platform that integrates social media engagement with cryptocurrency mining and
NFT functionality. Additional terms apply to specific use cases:

1. SMART CONTRACT USAGE
   - The smart contracts included in this repository are provided for 
     educational and development purposes
   - Production deployment requires proper security audits and compliance checks
   - Users assume full responsibility for any financial losses or security 
     breaches resulting from smart contract usage

2. TOKEN ECONOMICS
   - The $FIN token described in this codebase is a utility token for the 
     Finova Network ecosystem
   - Token distribution, mining rates, and economic models are subject to 
     change based on network governance decisions
   - No guarantee is made regarding token value, utility, or market performance

3. REGULATORY COMPLIANCE
   - Users must comply with all applicable laws and regulations in their 
     jurisdiction
   - KYC/AML requirements may apply depending on usage and location
   - The project team reserves the right to restrict access in certain 
     jurisdictions

4. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
   - The Finova Network brand, trademarks, and proprietary algorithms are 
     protected intellectual property
   - Third-party integrations and partnerships require separate licensing 
     agreements
   - Community contributions are welcomed under the same MIT license terms

5. SECURITY AND LIABILITY
   - This software is provided without warranty of any kind
   - Users are responsible for securing their private keys, seed phrases, 
     and digital assets
   - The development team is not liable for any losses, damages, or security 
     breaches

6. ANTI-BOT AND FAIR USE
   - The platform implements sophisticated anti-bot mechanisms
   - Automated interactions, farming, or manipulation of the reward system 
     is prohibited
   - Violations may result in account suspension and forfeiture of rewards

7. SOCIAL MEDIA INTEGRATION
   - Integration with third-party social media platforms is subject to their 
     respective terms of service
   - Users must maintain compliance with platform-specific policies
   - The project team is not responsible for changes in third-party APIs or 
     policies

8. DATA PRIVACY
   - User data is handled in accordance with applicable privacy laws
   - Blockchain transactions are public and immutable by nature
   - Off-chain personal data is protected according to our Privacy Policy

9. GOVERNANCE AND UPDATES
   - The project operates under a progressive decentralization model
   - Community governance through DAO mechanisms will be implemented over time
   - Software updates and protocol changes may occur with appropriate notice

10. EXPERIMENTAL TECHNOLOGY
    - This software utilizes experimental blockchain and AI technologies
    - Features may be modified, deprecated, or discontinued based on 
      technical requirements
    - Users should understand the risks associated with early-stage technology

